Description: include <wctype.h> instead of hand-declaring the isw*() functions
 arith.c declares iswalpha/iswalnum/iswdigit/iswspace itself rather than
 including <wctype.h>, on the assumption that pulling in the header is not worth
 it. musl defines those functions as macros, so the hand-written extern
 declarations clash with the real ones and arith.c fails to compile. Including
 the standard header is correct on every libc.
Origin: vendor, shell-versions
Forwarded: not-needed
Applied-Upstream: yes, 2.45 dropped the hand declarations

--- arith.c
+++ arith.c
@@ -38,11 +38,7 @@
  * (to[a-z]*) */
 
 
-/* we declare these functions instead of including <wctype.h> */
-extern int iswalpha(wint_t wc);
-extern int iswalnum(wint_t wc);
-extern int iswdigit(wint_t wc);
-extern int iswspace(wint_t wc);
+#include <wctype.h>
 
 
 typedef struct word_T {
